The paper deals with problems related to computational geometry, graph theory, and combinatorics. Specifically, it discusses counting crossing-free geometric graphs, computing the simplicial depth of a point in a set of points, and computing the number of facets of a polytope with few vertices. These topics are all closely related to the subfields of computational geometry (cs.CG), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), graph theory (cs.GT), and computational complexity (cs.CC). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper.
